<p><b>Curtis Lee Mayfield</b> (June 3, 1942 – December 26, 1999) was an American <a href="/wiki/Soul_music" title="Soul music">soul</a>, <a href="/wiki/Rhythm_and_blues" title="Rhythm and blues">R&amp;B</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Funk" title="Funk">funk</a> singer, songwriter, and record producer best known for his anthemic music with <a href="/wiki/The_Impressions_(American_band)" title="The Impressions (American band)" class="mw-redirect">The Impressions</a> and composing the <a href="/wiki/Super_Fly_(soundtrack)" title="Super Fly (soundtrack)">soundtrack</a> to the <a href="/wiki/Blaxploitation" title="Blaxploitation">blaxploitation</a> film <i><a href="/wiki/Super_Fly_(film)" title="Super Fly (film)">Super Fly</a>.</i> From these works and others, he was highly regarded as a pioneer of funk and of politically conscious African-American music.<sup id="cite_ref-HallOfFame_0-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-HallOfFame-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1" title=""><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup> He was also a <a href="/wiki/Multi-instrumentalist" title="Multi-instrumentalist">multi-instrumentalist</a> who played the <a href="/wiki/Guitar" title="Guitar">guitar</a>, <a href="/wiki/Bass_guitar" title="Bass guitar">bass</a>, <a href="/wiki/Piano" title="Piano">piano</a>, <a href="/wiki/Saxophone" title="Saxophone">saxophone</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Drum" title="Drum">drums</a>.</p>
